Claims WHAT IS CLAIMED IS: 1. An integrated valve assembly, comprising: an integrally molded one-piece housing, comprising: a central fuel funnel; a platform surrounding the central fuel funnel; a valve receptacle adjacent the central fuel funnel; and a pathway extending from the valve receptacle towards the platform; and a roll-over valve cartridge in the valve receptacle, the roll-over valve cartridge comprising a float, a roll-over sealing member, a float sleeve, and an orifice, the roll-over valve cartridge configured for fluid exchange through the float sleeve and the orifice in an open condition, and configured for the float to rise in liquid to abut the sealing member against the orifice in a closed condition, wherein the orifice is in fluid communication with the pathway. 2. The integrated valve assembly of claim 1 , wherein the platform further comprises a first platform port, and wherein the pathway is integrally molded to the first platform port. 3. The integrated valve assembly of claim 2, further comprising a second platform port and a top cap, wherein the top cap fluidly connects the first platform port to the second platform port. 4. The integrated valve assembly of claim 3, wherein the top cap is welded to the platform. 5. The integrated valve assembly of claim 2, wherein the pathway comprises a first pyramidal portion comprising a wide base and a truncated narrow end and a second pyramidal portion comprising a wide base and a truncated narrow end, wherein the wide base of the second pyramidal portion connects to the valve receptacle, wherein the wide base of the first pyramidal portion connects to the platform, and wherein the truncated narrow end of the first pyramidal portion connects to the truncated narrow end of the second pyramidal portion. 6. The integrated valve assembly of claim 1 , wherein the pathway connects to canister ducting configured for directing fluid away from the integrated valve assembly. 7. The integrated valve assembly of claim 1 , wherein the fuel funnel comprises an integrally molded lip for interfacing with a lid lock mechanism. 8. The integrated valve assembly of claim 1 , wherein the roll-over valve cartridge further comprises a first chamber within the float sleeve, the first chamber accommodating the float and roll-over sealing member, wherein the roll-over valve cartridge further comprises a second chamber accommodating an integrated make-up air and over-pressure 

 relief valve, and wherein the orifice passes through a plate between the first chamber and the second chamber. 9. The integrated valve assembly of claim 8, wherein: the plate comprises a valve seat in the second chamber, the valve seat circumscribing the orifice, the integrated make-up air and over-pressure relief valve comprises: a disc comprising a central hole; a hollow neck adjoining the central hole, the hollow neck comprising a tapered end extending away from the central hole; and a sealing member configured to reciprocate within the hollow neck between the central hole and the tapered end based on a fluid pressure on the sealing member, and the disc is configured to reciprocate in the second chamber between a position abutting the valve seat and a position spaced from the valve seat based on a fluid pressure on the disc. 10. The integrated valve assembly of claim 9, wherein the integrated make-up air and over-pressure relief valve does not comprise a spring. 11. The integrated valve assembly of claim 9, wherein the sealing member lifts away from the central hole to seal against the hollow neck when a higher than ambient fluid pressure is exerted on the sealing member, and wherein the sealing member releases away from the hollow neck in the presence of a vacuum condition. 12. The integrated valve assembly of claim 9, wherein the disc is configured to be in the position abutting the valve seat in the presence of a first vapor pressure that is in a range greater than or equal to ambient fluid pressure, but is configured to be in the position spaced from the valve seat in the presence of a second vapor pressure greater than the first vapor pressure. 13. The integrated valve assembly of claim 9, further comprising a cartridge cap for restricting the extent to which the disc reciprocates to the spaced position. 14. The integrated valve assembly of claim 9, wherein the valve receptacle comprises an extension for restricting the extent to which the disc reciprocates to the spaced position. 15. The integrated valve assembly of claim 8, wherein the second chamber comprises mounting extensions, and wherein the valve receptacle comprises a press-fit receptacle for receiving the mounting extensions. 16. The integrated valve assembly of claim 1 further comprising a support rib integrally molded between the central fuel funnel, the pathway, and the valve receptacle. 17. A fuel tank assembly, comprising: a fuel tank comprising a fuel tank interface and a canister port, the fuel tank interface comprising an opening for a fuel funnel; 

 a conduit mounted to the canister port; a mid plate affixed inside the fuel tank to an area surrounding the fuel tank interface; an integrally molded one-piece housing fixed to the fuel tank interface, the housing comprising: a central fuel funnel; a platform surrounding the central fuel funnel; a valve receptacle adjacent the central fuel funnel; and a pathway extending from the valve receptacle towards the platform, the pathway fluidly connected to the conduit; and a roll-over valve cartridge in the valve receptacle, the roll-over valve cartridge comprising a float, a roll-over sealing member, a float sleeve, and an orifice, the roll-over valve cartridge configured for fluid exchange through the float sleeve and the orifice in an open condition, and configured for the float to rise in liquid to abut the sealing member against the orifice in a closed condition, wherein the orifice is in fluid communication with the pathway. 18. The fuel tank assembly of claim 17, wherein the platform further comprises a first platform port, wherein the pathway is integrally molded to the first platform port, and wherein the first platform port fluidly communicates with the conduit. 19. The fuel tank assembly of claim 18, wherein the pathway comprises a first pyramidal portion comprising a wide base and a truncated narrow end and a second pyramidal portion comprising a wide base and a truncated narrow end, wherein the wide base of the second pyramidal portion connects to the valve receptacle, wherein the wide base of the first pyramidal portion connects to the platform, and wherein the truncated narrow end of the first pyramidal portion connects to the truncated narrow end of the second pyramidal portion. 20. The fuel tank assembly of claim 18, further comprising a second platform port and a top cap, wherein the top cap fluidly connects the first platform port to the second platform port, and wherein the top cap is mounted outside the fuel tank. 21. The fuel tank assembly of claim 20, wherein the fuel tank interface further comprises a conduit port, wherein the conduit is mounted to the conduit port to fluidly communicate through the second platform port, through the top cap, and through the first platform port to the pathway. 22. The fuel tank assembly of claim 17, wherein the fuel funnel comprises an integrally molded lip for interfacing with a lid lock mechanism. 23. The fuel tank assembly of claim 22, wherein the housing further comprises a support rib spanning between the lid lock mechanism and the platform. 24. The fuel tank assembly of claim 17, wherein the roll-over valve cartridge further comprises a first chamber within the float sleeve, the first chamber accommodating the float and roll-over sealing member, wherein the roll-over valve cartridge further comprises a second chamber accommodating an integrated make-up air and over-pressure relief valve, and wherein the orifice passes through a plate between the first chamber and the second chamber. 25. The fuel tank assembly of claim 24, wherein: the plate comprises a valve seat in the second chamber, the valve seat circumscribing the orifice, the integrated make-up air and over-pressure relief valve comprises: a disc comprising a central hole; a hollow neck adjoining the central hole, the hollow neck comprising a tapered end extending away from the central hole; and a sealing member configured to reciprocate within the hollow neck between the central hole and the tapered end based on a fluid pressure on the sealing member, and the disc is configured to reciprocate in the second chamber between a position abutting the valve seat and a position spaced from the valve seat based on a fluid pressure on the disc. 26. The fuel tank assembly of claim 25, wherein the sealing member lifts away from the central hole to seal against the hollow neck when a higher than ambient fluid pressure within the fuel tank is exerted on the sealing member, and wherein the sealing member releases away from the hollow neck in the presence of a vacuum condition in the fuel tank. 27. The fuel tank assembly of claim 25, wherein the disc is configured to be in the position abutting the valve seat in the presence of a first vapor pressure that is in a range greater than or equal to ambient fluid pressure within the fuel tank, but is configured to be in the position spaced from the valve seat in the presence of a second vapor pressure greater than the first vapor pressure. 28. The fuel tank assembly of claim 25, wherein the valve receptacle comprises an extension for restricting the extent to which the disc reciprocates to the spaced position. 29. The fuel tank assembly of claim 28, wherein the second chamber comprises mounting extensions, and wherein the valve receptacle comprises a press-fit receptacle for receiving the mounting extensions. 30. The fuel tank assembly of claim 17 further comprising a support rib integrally molded between the central fuel funnel, the pathway, and the valve receptacle. 31. The fuel tank assembly of claim 17, further comprising a tank lid, the tank lid comprising a lid seal, wherein the lid seal directly interfaces with the central fuel funnel to fluidly seal the tank lid to fuel tank.
